# Frontend React Standards

## General

- Keep components thin and logic-free; move logic into custom hooks.
- Prefer flat file structure — avoid nested component folders unless reuse demands it.
- Define subcomponents only used by one parent in the same file, above that component.
- In array method callbacks (`.map`, `.filter`, `.reduce`, etc.), prefer short single-letter params for concise callbacks.

## Next.js

- Default to Server Components; use Client Components only at interactive leaves.
- Use the modern App Router (`app/` directory) for layouts and page structures.
- Fetch data in Server Components (`async` components, direct `await`) — never in `useEffect`.

## Functions

- Components (pages, layouts, exported React components): function declarations (`export default function Page() {}`).
- Everything else (hooks, callbacks, helpers): arrow functions.

## Types

- Use `type`, never `interface`.
- Define prop types immediately above the component that uses them.
- Import hooks/types from `"react"` by name (`import { useState }`) — no namespace access (`React.useState`).

## Exports

- Next.js special files (`page`, `layout`, `loading`, `error`, `template`, `not-found`): default export (framework requirement).
- Route handlers (`route.ts`): named exports per HTTP method.
- Everything else: named exports. Keep internal helpers/subcomponents/types unexported unless reused elsewhere.

## Styling

- Embrace Tailwind's utility-first filosophy. Extend `globals.css` only for styles missing globally, not one-offs. 
- Prefer `flex`/`grid`/`gap`/container padding over per-child spacing.
- Design-system tokens as CSS custom properties: `--color-bg-main`, `--color-bg-surface`, `--color-text-main`, `--color-text-muted`.


## Verification

After frontend changes, from `frontend/`:

\`\`\`bash
npm run lint
npm run build
\`\`\`